Tatopani, Sindupalchowk. An organisation have provided us this waving machine. They took our product and give us money. I m able to spend money for daily needs that I dont get in relief. SO if i could continue this work I could be self dependent, I have not hope anything from government .

Tatopani, Sindupalchok. We cannot live in this camp forever. There should be a permanent solution. It may not come at once. But government should plan and try to help us. I hope we could go home soon , rebuild it and settle there.

Tatopani, Sindupalchowk. We dont know when we could go to our village.I hope to find some work here to earn some money. We have not moved into the house. There are major damages in the houses. We have not get any relief from government. All we get was help from neighbours. They provided us vegetables to eat. IT would be great if I could get easy loan to rebuild my house.

My house was totally damaged by the first hit of earthquake. We moved to our another home. My house was like 4 and half storeyed.As you see I am still removing the conceretes from here. I am doing this on my own. I got no help from government to remove these conceretes.

No i didnot get any kind of relief from government. No government officials have come to visit us. As I lost my one home, I immediately migrate to the compound my another house. I was hit by bunch of bricks during earthquake. The neighbors helped me and treated me. I got a tent from a local club. I hope to get better job in future.

The most important thing is shelter where we can be safe. Earthquake has done damages to my house. It is to be repaired. After rebuilding my priority is employment.

We didnot take any kind of relief. Our house is safe and we are thankful to god. We donot need any relief but seeing the difficulties of earthquake victims I pray they get proper relief.

I live in rent. The house I live in is in good condition. I hope I could do some business to earn money and build my own house. Talking about relief I have enough for me and my family . We dont find government distributing relief to the people of this area. Lets hope victims will be provided what they need in future.

We could only manage tripal from INGO as relief. Some damages are done by earthquake in my house. The government engineer has told us it can be repaired. But we have to repair that at our own cost and government can do nothing about it.We are looking forward to repair the house.

Our neighbours helped us get a tripal and we stayed under it for months. The government official have not come here to visit us. Well we can do things on our own and We need nothing from government. There are some damages done by earthquake in the house but we will repair it.

We got tripal and medicine from our neighbours. We didnot get any relief from government. Our house is safe . Well some repairements are to be done but we need no other relief.I need employment to better my life.

Rebuilding is our first priority. We have not moved into the house. I have a shop in the ground floor. We open the shop at morning, do our business and We go to tent at night. I think it is risky to move in now. Repairments are to be done. But no government officials have come to see the condition of our house. Hence we are not able to get the card promised by government. With out card we cannot get competations or monetary aid to repair our house.

My house fell down after the first hit of earthquake. We got nothing from any one for months. Then I went to CDO office and gave the evidence of my damaged house. They provided me with a red card for my house and after some time they gave me 15000 rupees. I hope we could get loan in low interest from government so that i could rebuild my house.
I got a tripal from red cross. My house is in a good condition.So, I donot need anything more. I hope the real victims get the relief.
I didnot get any relief beacause i didnot need any. I bought a tripal so that i could run in to it when earthquake comes. My house is fine and i hope real victims get the relief.

I had two houses. One that was made of mud was destroyed by earthquake by the first hit. Another house is concrete and earthquake has done some damages to it. Government has not give any compensation for my old house. They say people owning more than two houses cannot get monetary relief. We used to live in the old house. I think government should have give us monetary relief for the old house.
I dont think much damage is done in Mulpani except those old mud houses. Shelter is a basic need and I think government should help the real victims immediately and manage for their shelter.

My son managed tripal from his office. We sat under that tripal for days due to earthquake threat. The condition of my house is good. We dont need anything from anyone but I hope the real victims get the releif they want.

We need no relief. We needed tripal after the first hit of earthquake. But we couldnot manage it for more than a week. We are lucky that our house is in a good condition. I pray that the real victims get releifs.

We didnot get any sorts of relief stuffs. There are some damages in my house done by earthquake. One or Two engineer came to us and took a look over the house. They told us there is nothing to worry. And we are living in the house. I repaird all the damages at my own cost.

I am an old man. I have a wife. We live seperate from our two sons. I used to live in a house with a son but we live seperately. we had seperate kitchens and we used to be together only in the festivals. The first hit of earthquake made the house fall. My son got Rs 15000 from government for that old house. But I didnot get anything at all. I live in a very small cottage with my wife. I had no kitchen and i cook under sky. I have not got anything from any one. The powerful people here ignore me and dont listen to my problems. I am a poor old man and no body is going to help me.

Ofcourse my priority will be rebuilding. I lost my house and many stuff because of earthquake. I took the evidence of my loss and went to CDO office and I got Rs 15000. But my father didnot get anything from government and not from any organization. I m poor but I m trying to do something for my father and mother.

I didnot get any relief because we didnot ask for relief. We had a tripal and we lived under it during earthquake. We are thankful to god our house is safe. There are only few houses that fell down in Mulpani. But I donot think they are getting releifs properly.

Our house fell down by the first hit of earthquake. We cut down the house and now it has just one room. I and my husband live here. My son's family moved to that cottage. We made that cottage on our own. We didnot get any releif. No government official has come down here to take a look at us and not even the political leaders of this area. We found Rs 15000 from the government as a relief. But let me tell you it took 30 thousands to cut down this old house and Rs 5000 to make that cottage. And government gave us 15000 as a relief.

We got Rs 15000 as a releif from government and that is all we get. Our house fell down into the floor by the first hit and we live under the sky for the first day. Second day we managed old tripal on our own so that we could save our selves from rain. And then we build this cottage on our own. There was no participation of government in distribution of releif. but now we hope to get loan at low interest for rebuilding.
We didnot want any relief stuffs. Our house is safe and so we are happy.

I work as a volunteer in government relief programme. I loaded 100 sacks of rice in a vechile that was supposed to be for distributing in Mulpani. But only very few sack among that 100 were distributed in Mulpani. And I got some. I was amazed where was other sacks of rice taken.. My house is some damaged by earthquake and I want to maintain it.

I lost my house due to earthquake. I cut down the house and we have a room left. We got Rs 15000 from government as relief. Except that we didnot get anything. And we donot need anything else. Government is talking about providing victims loan at low interest. I am waiting for that loan to rebuild my house. Employment is my another priority after rebuilding.
We didnot get anything from anyone. I live in this cottage. I hope I would get some kind of relief in coming future that could easy my life.
We need no relief. Our house is safe and we are thankful to god. We dont need anything but we hope real victims get the releif.
Our house is safe and we donot need any kind of relief. There are only some old houses in Mulpani that were affected by earthquake. The most of people are not affected here.

We need no relief stuffs. I am also social worker and I would suggest you to go to the place like sindupalchowk, nuwakot , gorkha where the people are really affected.Here in Mulpani only some people are affected.

I am from Dolakha. I passed my childhood in hetauda in orphanage. I have passed my bachelors degree. I had a home in Dolakha and I lost it because of earthquake. Here in Mulpani I live in my sister's house. Despite of my degree I have no job. And I am looking for one. If you could give me a job it would be really helpful for me. contact no is 9741014706
Our house is safe an we dont need any kind of relief. We hope people really affected by earthquake get releif.

We didnot get any relief. We wanted tripal after the first hit of earthquake . We didnot get them and we managed them ourselves.Our house is safe and we dont need any reliefs. We just hope the real victims get the relief they require.

We got tripal from INGO. We didnot ask for any other kind of relief. Our house is safe and we are happy . My priority is employment. I am studying bachelor and as soon as i pass out, I hope to get a job.
My house is safe and I thank god for this. I want have an employment in future.That is all I want. Our family doesnot want any kind of relief because we dont need them.
We want no reliefs. Our house is safe. We had to manage tripal in the begining. We managed them on our wown. We have what we need. I hope real victims get proper relief.

We need no relief. We wanted tripal at the begining but we managed it ourselves.I have my own shop and i make enough out of it for my self. I hope real victims of sindupalchok gorkha nuwakot dhading etc i mean the real victims get relief.

We are from middle class family. Our house is not affected by earthquake that much. I have maintained it already. I hope the real victims get the relief.and government will perform its responsibilites well
Our house is safe and we dont need any relief. Some people here in Mulpani are earthquake victims but they are not provided with any sorts of releif.

Earthquake has not affected our physical assets.We donot need relief for ourselves. Mulpani is not that affected by earthquake. We can see some old houses affected by earthquake. But they are not getting reliefs. The responsible person are not doing their duty and so earthquake victims are not getting enough reliefs.
